      One variable in the equation of the elliptic paraboloid will be raised to the first power; above, this is the <m>z</m> variable. The paraboloid will <q>open</q> in the direction of this variable's axis. Thus <m>x= y^2/a^2+z^2/b^2</m> is an elliptic paraboloid that opens along the <m>x</m>-axis.


